"""
Substrate Derivation of c2 Lattice Rank — Empirical Verification.

Tests the two pre-registered claims:
  Part 1 (Universality): c2 = round(R^n + (x_term - 1)) in float64 is exactly
    representable as j · ulp(f) for some integer j, when x_term is in the
    Sterbenz-applicable region.
  Part 2 (Rank bound): max |j| ≤ a(n) where a(2) ≤ 3/2 and a(3) ≤ 4.

Preregistry: Build_Docs/Reports/c2_lattice_substrate_derivation/preregistry.md
"""
from __future__ import annotations

